Up for sale/trade is an uncommon 91/59 Mosin Nagant carbine. 91/59's were 91/30's that were cut down to a 20" barrel sometime during the cold war. They are lighter than the M44 Mosins and quick handling (similar to an m38) while still keeping the same high power 54r round. The bluing and stock on this particular rifle are excellent, the trigger is also very light and crisp unlike your typical 91/30. The serial numbers are all matching and it passes headspace. It is a beautiful example, cheap to shoot, and very powerful. 

Asking $300 or The trades I am looking for are Finnish Mosin Variants, a Makarov Pistol or current gunbot price on .40 s&w ammo. If you have anything youd like to trade or interested in buying let me know. Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  Rare & Collectible Military Ammo
postcontent:
Hey everyone. I've just about finished selling my life long collection of military small arms from around the world so now I've opened up my ammo & accessories safe and I'll be selling it's contents as I have time.  

All of this ammo has been stored in my air conditioned home inside a dehumidified safe.   

A few things to keep in mind: First most of this ammo was originally designed for either military or LE use, and a lot of it is either steel jacketed, steel core or both. So any ammo I describe as magnetic means that it will potentially penetrate targets much deeper than standard commercial ammo. Therefore please be extra cautious with your backstop if you decide to shoot any of it. I feel quite sure that it all will fire so be careful. Second any of the tracer ammo can and will start fires. So again please use with all due caution. Here is the ammo in this lot:  

(2) 20 round boxes 6.5 x 55 Swedish Mauser. Brass case, non corrosive & magnetic. Very clean military surplus ammo. $35 for both boxes. 

(2) 20 round boxes 6.5 x 55 Swedish Mauser with wooden bullet. This ammo is intended as a blank round but requires a special adapter to shred the bullet at the muzzle. Without this adapter the wooden bullet is dangerous and could be fatal at close range so use caution when firing. $15 for both boxes. 

(5) 10 round boxes of German 8x56R for use in Steyr Straight Pull rifles & carbines. This ammo is brass case, corrosive and magnetic. It's unbelievably clean for being made in 1938. This ammo is truly collectible and the box plus every round is stamped with the German Acceptance Mark. Each box has 10 rounds loaded on 2 stripper clips. These clips & empty boxes sell on auction sites for just about as much as I'm asking for the real live ammo. Price is $20 a box or $80 for all five. 

(1) 50 round box of Kynoch 7mm Mauser loaded on 5 round chargers. Ammo is brass case, corrosive & very magnetic. This box is unopened so I did not want to disturb it. However I have a partial box of the same ammo and it's unbelievably clean... looks like it was just made, but it was actually produced in January 1938, and it's noted right on the box. Vintage Kynoch is among the most collectible ammo available. Asking $100 for the box. 

(1) 100 round bulk box of 7mm Mauser made by FN Belgium in 1936. Ammo was made for Venezuela, and it's brass case, corrosive and very magnetic. This ammo is also in unbelievable condition for it's age. Cases are bright and there are no signs or corrosion or deterioration at all. Very collectible and perfect to display with your South American Mauser(s).  $75 for the box. 

I do have additional quantities of some, but not all of the ammo listed above. So just ask if you are looking for more. 

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  HK Style 26.5mm Flare Pistol.
postcontent:
This is a very well made copy of the HK P2A1 flare pistol from the 70's & 80's. This one was made in Poland by Radom Arsenal (note the circle 11 Radom symbol in the pictures). I've compared this pistol side by side with the HK and they appear identical to me except for how they are marked.

This particular pistol is in good - very good condition, but it does show some signs of use. No rust, or serious blemishes - rather just signs of normal military use.

Pistol comes with a canvas flap holster, a 26.5mm cleaning rod and a rope lanyard strap.

Asking $100 with pickup in the Brandon area. Must be 18 or older to purchase.

Note 26.5mm flare, parachute & smoke ammo is available online from several sources including Dan's Ammo, Ammunition To Go and Sportsman Guide. The 26.5mm cartridge is a jumbo round at 1 inch diameter, and there is no comparison to the 12 gauge plastic pistols & ammo that are so common today. The 26.5mm pistols & ammo were designed for military use and firing them is quite spectacular!
